Em strikes:
1st: E to e
2nd: e to E (Slowly, to touch each string)

The rest:
Yellow bird, you are not 'lone in singing and in flying on,
in laughing and in leaving.
Willow weeping in the water, waving to the river daughters,
swaying in the ripples and the reeds.
On a trip to Cirrus Minor, saw a crater in the sun
a thousand miles of moonlight later.

